[[Image:ThermalFissionYield.svg|thumb|350px|Fission product yields by mass for [[thermal neutron]] fission of [[Uranium-235|U-235]], [[Pu-239]], a combination of the two typical of current nuclear power reactors, and [[Uranium-233|U-233]] used in the [[thorium cycle]].]]
On this page, a discussion of each of the main elements in the [[fission product]] mixture from the [[nuclear fission]] of an [[actinide]] such as [[uranium]] or [[plutonium]] is set out by element.
{{isotope colour chart|}}

